Update Rename utilities.Utilities to utilities.InitializationToolbox. Modify utilities.InitializationToolbox.get_hemodynamic_parameter_prior_distributions. It now return a pd.dataframe. Rename InitializationToolbox.get_hemodynamic_parameter_prior_distributions_as_dataframe to InitializationToolbox.get_expanded_hemodynamic_parameter_prior_distributions and modify it according the above modification.

Rename and restructure Rename utilities.py to toolboxes.py. All toolboxes used by DCM_RNN package will be put in it. Rename utilities.Utilities to toolboxes.Initialization. Functions in this toolbox are used to do parameter initialization. Add parameter_unit.py and parameter_unit.ParameterUnit. ParameterUnit will work as an unit containing all needed parameters and related operations. It calls toolboxes.Initialization.

Package structure rearrangement Remove parameter_unit.py Move the functionalities of population.py into CBI.py. Remove population.py Use CBI.Project to maintain a study. CBI.Project.plan_a_experiment() to set up all experimental parameters, like n_node, n_stimuli, t_delta, and u CBI.Project.recruit_a_subject() to set up all parameters related to subjects, like ABC and hemodynamic parameters, following experimental settings. It returns a Scan_ready_sheet object, containing all information needed for a scan. CBI.Scanner contains functionalities of a scanner. CBI.Scanner.make_a_scan() takes in a Scan_ready_sheet object and make a scan accordingly. It returns a Scan_result, which contains the Scan_ready_sheet and u, x, h, and y readings. Scan_result is the object feeding into following analysis.

Package structure rearrangement Project -> Study -> Study.plan_a_experiment -> -> Study.recruit_a_subject -> Study.make_scan_ready_sheets - scan_ready_sheet -> -> Scanner.make_a_scan() - scan_result -> Study.make_reports - reports -> further analysis
Project: inherits from dict, containing the information common to all its studies. Its dictionary items are studies; its attributes are used to store common information. Project.create_a_study() # create a study with project info, if not enough, more info is needed
Study: inherits from Object Study.experiment_plan, dictionary Study.subjects, dictionary with subID Study.scan_ready_sheets, dictionary with all info needed for scanning Study.scan_results, dictionary, each key is subID, each value is a dictionary containing x, h, and y Srudy.reports, dictionary, each key is subID, each value is a dictionary containing all above info
Study.plan_a_experiment() Study.generate_stimuli() Study.recruit_a_subject() Study.make_scan_ready_sheets() # used to join information of plan_a_experiment and recruit_a_subject Study.make_reports() # used to join information of scan_ready_sheets and scan_results Study.show_experiment_plan()
Scanner: inherits from Object Scanner.make_a_scan(), takes in scan_ready_sheets

Update toolboxes.Initialization Put hard-coded parameters into class attributes so that they can be accessed and modified with easy. Unify random number generation with uniform distribution with low and high. All member functions are modified accordingly. randomly_generate_sparse_A_matrix has all functionalities of randomly_generate_A_matrix, so remove randomly_generate_A_matrix and rename randomly_generate_sparse_A_matrix as randomly_generate_A_matrix

# package structure rearrangement and add parameter graph THE MOST IMPORTANT THING IS KEEPING INTEGRALTITY AND CONSISTENCE OF DATA UNIT. Class DataUnit should have a hidden dictionary recording all the parameters and scanned data. It should only be written by DataUnit's methods to keep integrality and consistence but should be read easily. Data should be put in to levels. If one parameter uses other parameters on at most n level, it in at n+1 level. Ideally, parameters should be specified only from higher level to lower level and it should be pretty easy to generate lower level parameters randomly with higher level parameters. In the fully random case, only level 0 parameters are necessary to be set. Whenever one wants to set a parameter, DataUnit should check its consistence with existing parameters. But it may be too complex and time consuming. Now, use it as a guide line rather than strict requirement. Build parameter level relationship graph. Previous Project, Study, Scanner structure are not necessary so are not used.
ParameterGraph and ParameterGraph.generate_gv_file are added. They plot parameter graph with dot tool to show dependency between parameters. Nicely, the parameter level are very easy to read from the graph, so it's no longer needed to be tracked manually.
Update ParameterGraph.generate_gv_file level lables are added and parameters at the same level are put into the same rank
DataUnit inherits from Initialization and add DataUnit.abstract_flag

Use category mechanism for secured parameter assignment. Base on prerequisites, put parameters in to 3 categories. Category one: no prerequisites, should be assigned value directly Category two: with prerequisite and has if_random_ flag in prerequisites, one needs to check flag before assign Category three: with prerequisite and has no flag, should not be assigned directly, its value should be derived by its prerequisites.
Add DataUnit.categorize_parameters Add DataUnit.check_prerequisites Add DataUnit.set_category_one_parameter Add DataUnit.set_category_two_parameter (not complete) Add DataUnit.set_category_three_parameter (not complete)
Update parameter graph
Remove individual hemodynamic parameter from parameter graph

Upgrade ParameterGraph, adding all kinds of parameter relation operation in it Move initializer to the first level since now it's inherited directly. Add ParameterGraph.forerunner2descendant Add ParameterGraph.level_para2para_level Add ParameterGraph.get_para_level_mapping Add ParameterGraph.make_graph to replace Parametergraph.generate_gv_file Move abstract_flag from DataUnit to ParameterGraph Move categorize_parameters from DataUnite to PrameterGraph Add ParameterGraph.para_category2category_para Add ParameterGraph.get_para_category_mapping
class DataUnit inherits both Initialization and ParameterGraph

Upgrade ParameterGraph and add tests for it Now _para_forerunner and _level_para are hidden attributes. All relationship dictionary should be obtained by calling get_ function. ParameterGraph methods list: __init__ check_parameter_relation get_para_forerunner_mapping forerunner2descendant get_para_descendant_mapping level_para2para_level get_level_para_mapping get_para_level_mapping get_para_category_mapping para_category2category_para get_category_para_mapping abstract_flag make_graph
